(135, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/mb-pcnNNH3w/pressforward-rss-reader-inside-of-wordpress'' title=''    With the impending shutdown of Google Reader on July 1st, I’ve been looking for Feedreader alternatives. I happened to stumble across a recently developed plugin called PressForward. Developed for the Roy Rosenzweig Center for History and New Media at George Mason University by Aram Zucker-Scharff, Boone B. Gorges, and Jeremy Boggs, PressForward provides [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: PressForward – RSS Reader Inside Of WordPress</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/3Aw2itwe0Y8/wordpress-3-6-status-update'' title=''I’ve received some emails and Twitter responses asking me if I knew any information as to when WordPress 3.6 would be released. After looking around, it was clear that not a lot of information about the upcoming release is available. I stopped by the WordPress developers chat today to figure out what was going on and here is what I know. There is still quite [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: WordPress 3.6 Status Update</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/06/19/billie-hillier-how-to-make-readers-search-engines-love-your-content/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Billie Hillier: How to Make Readers &amp; Search Engines Love Your Content</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/06/19/joe-boydston-free-speech-free-press-free-software/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Joe Boydston: Free Speech, Free Press, Free Software</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/6d3CksO7O78/does-sex-sell-wordpress-themes'' title=''In what is the first time I’ve ever seen the issue raised, WP Garage brings up the topic of whether scandalous images sell more WordPress Themes? In the examples Rebecca Markowitz provides within the post, there are a couple of images featuring women covered in different colors of paint while barely having any clothes on. The third example shows an image of  [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: Does Sex Sell WordPress Themes?</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
